Oranda's CSS makes use of cascade layers to scope CSS and make it simpler to override styles. To override themed styles, say on a <p> element, place it inside a layer called overrides. @layer overrides { p { color: aquamarine; }
} Alternately, CSS that is not defined within a layer has precedence over all layered CSS, so this will also work. p { color: aquamarine;
}

